  "name": "Suppression Emails",
  "body": "<p>In JetSend, you can add and manage the suppression emails on the Suppression Emails page. In Navigation, go to EMAIL and then select Suppression.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"User-added image\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png\" width=\"696\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"height: 344px; width: 696px\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/1.05T5g00000Ao6V1EAJ.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></p>\n<p><br/>The Suppression Emails page shows all the email addresses that have been added for suppression and enables you to perform the following actions:</p>\n<ul><li>Add email addresses to which emails must be suppressed. We recommend that you add the email addresses that have unsubscribed from your services. You must also add the addresses that have caused email bounces.</li><li>Delete email addresses that no longer need to be suppressed.</li><li>Export the list of suppressed email addresses.</li></ul>",
